<% external_link_classes = "min-w-0 font-semibold wrap-anywhere underline hover:decoration-2 focus-visible:outline-hidden focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-primary-500 focus-visible:rounded-sm dark:text-white" %>

<div class="container mx-auto space-y-8 px-4 py-8">
  <h1 class="text-heading text-5xl font-bold">Accessibility Statement for IRIDA Next</h1>

  <section class="space-y-4" aria-labelledby="our-commitment-to-accessibility">
    <h2 id="our-commitment-to-accessibility" class="text-heading text-4xl font-bold">
      Our Commitment to Accessibility
    </h2>

    <p class="text-body text-lg">
      IRIDA Next is committed to ensuring that our application is accessible to all users, including those with
      disabilities. We are dedicated to providing a user experience that is inclusive and compliant with established
      accessibility standards.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="space-y-4" aria-labelledby="accessibility-standards-and-conformance">
    <h2 id="accessibility-standards-and-conformance" class="text-heading text-4xl font-bold">
      Accessibility Standards and Conformance
    </h2>

    <p class="text-body text-lg">
      IRIDA Next strives to meet the
      <a href="https://www.w3.org/WAI/WCAG21/quickref/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="<%= external_link_classes %>">Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) 2.1<span class="sr-only"> (opens in a new tab)</span></a>
      Level AA standard. This includes:
    </p>

    <ul class="text-body list-inside list-disc space-y-1 text-lg">
      <li>
        <strong>Perceivable</strong>: Information and user interface components must be presented in ways that are
        perceivable to all users
      </li>

      <li>
        <strong>Operable</strong>: User interface components and navigation must be operable through multiple methods
      </li>

      <li><strong>Understandable</strong>: Information and user interface operation must be understandable</li>
      <li><strong>Robust</strong>: Content must be compatible with current and future assistive technologies</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <h2 class="text-heading text-4xl font-bold">Accessible Features</h2>

  <section class="space-y-4" aria-labelledby="navigation-and-structure">
    <h3 id="navigation-and-structure" class="text-heading text-3xl font-bold">Navigation and Structure</h3>

    <ul class="text-body list-inside list-disc space-y-1 text-lg">
      <li>Semantic HTML markup ensures proper document structure</li>
      <li>Logical heading hierarchy (H1 through H6) for screen reader navigation</li>
      <li>Skip navigation links to bypass repetitive content</li>
      <li>Keyboard-accessible navigation throughout the application</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="space-y-4" aria-labelledby="interactive-elements">
    <h3 id="interactive-elements" class="text-heading text-3xl font-bold">Interactive Elements</h3>

    <ul class="text-body list-inside list-disc space-y-1 text-lg">
      <li>All interactive elements (buttons, links, form controls) are keyboard accessible</li>
      <li>Clear focus indicators for keyboard navigation</li>
      <li>Proper ARIA labels and roles for custom components</li>
      <li>Form labels clearly associated with input fields</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="space-y-4" aria-labelledby="visual-accessibility">
    <h3 id="visual-accessibility" class="text-heading text-3xl font-bold">Visual Accessibility</h3>

    <ul class="text-body list-inside list-disc space-y-1 text-lg">
      <li>Sufficient color contrast ratios (WCAG AA compliant)</li>
      <li>Text is resizable without loss of functionality</li>
      <li>No reliance on color alone to convey information</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="space-y-4" aria-labelledby="assistive-technology-support">
    <h3 id="assistive-technology-support" class="text-heading text-3xl font-bold">Assistive Technology Support</h3>

    <ul class="text-body list-inside list-disc space-y-1 text-lg">
      <li>Compatible with screen readers (NVDA and JAWS)</li>
      <li>Proper semantic markup and ARIA attributes</li>
      <li>Alternative text for images and visual content</li>
      <li>Accessible data tables with proper header associations</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="space-y-4" aria-labelledby="keyboard-navigation">
    <h3 id="keyboard-navigation" class="text-heading text-3xl font-bold">Keyboard Navigation</h3>

    <ul class="text-body list-inside list-disc space-y-1 text-lg">
      <li>Full functionality available via keyboard</li>
      <li>Logical tab order through interactive elements</li>
      <li>Escape key functionality for closing dialogs</li>
      <li>Proper keyboard shortcuts for widgets</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="space-y-4" aria-labelledby="motion-and-animation">
    <h3 id="motion-and-animation" class="text-heading text-3xl font-bold">Motion and Animation</h3>

    <ul class="text-body list-inside list-disc space-y-1 text-lg">
      <li>No flashing or blinking content</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="space-y-4" aria-labelledby="how-to-report-accessibility-issues">
    <h2 id="how-to-report-accessibility-issues" class="text-heading text-4xl font-bold">
      How to Report Accessibility Issues
    </h2>

    <p class="text-body text-lg">
      We take accessibility seriously and welcome feedback to help us improve. If you encounter an accessibility
      barrier, please report it by:
    </p>

    <ol class="text-body list-inside list-decimal space-y-4 text-lg">
      <li>
        <strong>Creating a GitHub Issue</strong>: Open an issue on our
        <a href="https://github.com/phac-nml/irida-next/issues" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="<%= external_link_classes %>">GitHub repository<span class="sr-only"> (opens in a new tab)</span></a>
        with:

        <ul class="mt-2 list-inside list-disc space-y-1 ps-5 text-lg">
          <li>A clear description of the accessibility barrier</li>
          <li>The browser and assistive technology used (if applicable)</li>
          <li>Steps to reproduce the issue</li>
          <li>Screenshots or screen reader output if possible</li>
          <li>Relevant WCAG criterion numbers</li>
        </ul>
      </li>

      <li>
        <strong>Email</strong>: Contact the
        <a href="mailto:gsp-psg@phac-aspc.gc.ca" class="<%= external_link_classes %>">GSP team<span class="sr-only"> (opens default email client)</span></a>.
      </li>
    </ol>
  </section>

  <section class="space-y-4" aria-labelledby="accessibility-improvement-process">
    <h2 id="accessibility-improvement-process" class="text-heading text-4xl font-bold">
      Accessibility Improvement Process
    </h2>

    <ul class="text-body list-inside list-disc space-y-1 text-lg">
      <li><strong>Regular Audits</strong>: Periodic accessibility audits using automated tools and manual testing</li>
      <li><strong>Screen Reader Testing</strong>: Testing with NVDA and JAWS</li>
      <li><strong>Keyboard Navigation Testing</strong>: Verification of keyboard-only navigation</li>
      <li><strong>Color Contrast Verification</strong>: Compliance with WCAG AA contrast requirements</li>
      <li><strong>User Feedback</strong>: Incorporation of feedback from users with disabilities</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="space-y-4" aria-labelledby="third-party-content-and-dependencies">
    <h2 id="third-party-content-and-dependencies" class="text-heading text-4xl font-bold">
      Third-Party Content and Dependencies
    </h2>

    <p class="text-body text-lg">
      IRIDA Next uses various third-party libraries and services. While we evaluate these for accessibility, we cannot
      guarantee full WCAG compliance for external content or services. If you encounter accessibility issues with
      third-party components, please report them to us so we can evaluate alternatives.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="space-y-4" aria-labelledby="version-information">
    <h2 id="version-information" class="text-heading text-4xl font-bold">Version Information</h2>

    <p class="text-body text-lg"><strong>Last Updated</strong>: June 2, 2026</p>
  </section>
</div>
